        "shape": "predefined-process"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "sticky-layer2-llm",
      "type": "sticky",
      "text": "**Layer 2 LLM**\n- We give the LLM the conversation history, active tasks, and all tools it has access to\n  - Currently this is around 15 tools\n- This LLM then says what tool to use (if any)",
      "color": "pink",
      "parentId": "page-frame",
      "geometry": {
        "x": 4160,
        "y": 2976,
        "width": 464,
        "height": 368
      },
      "style": {
        "shape": "note"
      },
      "author": "ford"
    },
    {
      "id": "sticky-3cases",
      "type": "sticky",
      "text": "**There are 3cases we need to consider for the tool calling**\n- No Task Needed\n  - This is a fallback for if we do not need to create a new task for the chat\n    - EX, we got here to search for loads, but are already preforming a search\n- Task Needed (and Enough Info)\n  - We have everything to do a task that the user wants done\n  - Enqueue the task\n- Tasked Need but More info Required\n  - We may want to run a tool, but in order to do that we need more context\n    - EX, search loads we need a destination and pickup)",
      "color": "blue",
      "parentId": "page-frame",
      "geometry": {
        "x": 4160,
        "y": 768,
        "width": 560,
        "height": 688
      },
      "style": {
        "shape": "note"
      },
      "author": "ford"
    },
    {
      "id": "sticky-agent-response",
      "type": "sticky",
      "text": "How does the agent know when to return the agent response?\n- The classic gemini API we return the function call response, but gemini then formats this into a user response\n- We the multi layer, the function call is like “determine new task”, the response will now not be the actual function response\n- We need an intermediary layer to convert the function output into a response",
      "color": "gray",
      "parentId": "page-frame",
      "geometry": {
        "x": 608,
        "y": 2976,
        "width": 608,
        "height": 480
      },
      "style": {
        "shape": "note"
      },
      "author": "ford"
    },
    {
      "id": "sticky-layer1-agent",
      "type": "sticky",
      "text": "**Layer 1 Agent**\n- Handles communication with the user.\n- The agent does not have knowledge of the all the tools in layer 2-N, but rather has a tool to say\n  - “We need a tool call, go figure out what task to enqueue”\n- This functions as the pass through to the more powerful LLM that may take longer to respond\n- The other tool could then see what tasks are currently running",
      "color": "pink",
      "parentId": "page-frame",
      "geometry": {
        "x": 1312,
        "y": 2976,
        "width": 608,
        "height": 480
      },
      "style": {
        "shape": "note"
      },
      "author": "ford"
    },
    {
      "id": "sticky-active-task-insertion",
      "type": "sticky",
      "text": "**Active Task Insertion**\n- Each message we will get all the tasks and their most recent state\n- This way if the user asks a question about an ongoing task, we will return to the user what is going on with that task in a conversational way\n- **KEY IDEA**\n  - Need the prompt to really detail how this process will work, ie, don’t make a new task if we are already doing that one",
      "color": "pink",
      "parentId": "page-frame",
      "geometry": {
        "x": 2016,
        "y": 2976,
        "width": 608,
        "height": 480
      },
      "style": {
        "shape": "note"
      },
      "author": "ford"
    },
    {
      "id": "sticky-alert-mechanism",
      "type": "sticky",
      "text": "**ALERT MECHANISM**\n- Alert mechanism is that on each message, in the prompt we will have functions that are completed, but have not be told to the user\n- We will instruct the LLM to always tell the user about the results of completed tasks and then call the function to say “we did that”\n- This function will then remove the completed task id from the list, essentially marking that task has been communicated to the user\n- These completed tasks, will be included in the system prompt",
      "color": "gray",
      "parentId": "page-frame",
      "geometry": {
        "x": 2720,
        "y": 2976,
        "width": 736,
        "height": 480
      },
      "style": {
        "shape": "note"
      },
      "author": "ford"
    }
  ],
